The Radisson Blu Hotel in Wroclaw, Poland is bubbling with life as the Super Eagles stars invited for Friday night’s friendly match against the Polish national team are already trooping in from their various bases. Super Eagles coach, Gernot Rohr invited 28 players for the Poland friendly as well as the Serbia test match coming up in London and from that list, 14 players have already arrived as at Tuesday morning with others expected in the course of the day. Those already on ground include the England-based duo of Alex Iwobi, Ola Aina, Mainz 05 defender Leon Balogun, William Troost Ekong, Tyronne Ebuehi and Brian Idowu who all arrived on Monday night. The latest set of arrivals include Moses Simon, Francis Uzoho, Elderson Echiejile, Stephen Eze, Joel Obi, Shehu Abdullahi, John Ogu and Kenneth Omeruo. 